    dc:description "FIGURES 9 – 14. Majerthrips and Sennithrips species. (9) M. barrowi micropterous female, ventral; (10) M. barrowi micropterous female, dorsal; (11) M. barrowi apterous female, metanotum and tergites I – II; (12) S. psomus, ventral; (13) S. psomus, dorsal; (14) S. psomus antenna. [ns = prothoracic notopleural suture; ss = metathoracic sternopleural suture]" ;
